[30;1m82 | [0m[35m    ## Description[0m
[30;1m83 | [0m[35m    This environment is a classic rocket trajectory optimization problem.[0m
[30;1m84 | [0m[35m    According to Pontryagin's maximum principle, it is optimal to fire the[0m
[30;1m85 | [0m[35m    engine at full throttle or turn it off. This is the reason why this[0m
[30;1m86 | [0m[35m    environment has discrete actions: engine on or off.[0m
[30;1m87 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m88 | [0m[35m    There are two environment versions: discrete or continuous.[0m

[30;1m596 | [0m[35m        if self.prev_shaping is not None:[0m

[30;1m29 | [0m[35m    ## Description[0m
[30;1m30 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m31 | [0m[35m    The Mountain Car MDP is a deterministic MDP that consists of a car placed stochastically[0m
[30;1m32 | [0m[35m    at the bottom of a sinusoidal valley, with the only possible actions being the accelerations[0m
[30;1m33 | [0m[35m    that can be applied to the car in either direction. The goal of the MDP is to strategically[0m
[30;1m34 | [0m[35m    accelerate the car to reach the goal state on top of the right hill. There are two versions[0m
[30;1m35 | [0m[35m    of the mountain car domain in gymnasium: one with discrete actions and one with continuous.[0m

[30;1m61 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m62 | [0m[35m    *position<sub>t+1</sub> = position<sub>t</sub> + velocity<sub>t+1</sub>*[0m
[30;1m63 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m64 | [0m[35m    where force = 0.001 and gravity = 0.0025. The collisions at either end are inelastic with the ve[0m
[30;1m65 | [0m[35m    upon collision with the wall. The position is clipped to the range `[-1.2, 0.6]` and[0m
[30;1m66 | [0m[35m    velocity is clipped to the range `[-0.07, 0.07]`.[0m

  Severity: [36mModerate[0m, Confidence: [36mLow[0m
  Filename: [33m/gymnasium-1.1.1/gymnasium/envs/classic_control/mountain_car.py[0m

[30;1m19 | [0m[35m    ## Description[0m
[30;1m20 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m21 | [0m[35m    The Mountain Car MDP is a deterministic MDP that consists of a car placed stochastically[0m
[30;1m22 | [0m[35m    at the bottom of a sinusoidal valley, with the only possible actions being the accelerations[0m
[30;1m23 | [0m[35m    that can be applied to the car in either direction. The goal of the MDP is to strategically[0m
[30;1m24 | [0m[35m    accelerate the car to reach the goal state on top of the right hill. There are two versions[0m
[30;1m25 | [0m[35m    of the mountain car domain in gymnasium: one with discrete actions and one with continuous.[0m
